290
00:11:20,620 --> 00:11:21,550
What does she do?

291
00:11:21,890 --> 00:11:22,820
She's a singer.

292
00:11:23,220 --> 00:11:24,200
A singer?

293
00:11:24,370 --> 00:11:25,830
She's a girl from Wenzhou.

294
00:11:25,910 --> 00:11:27,370
Her name is Zhuang Zhuang.

295
00:11:28,150 --> 00:11:29,480
Zhuang... Zhuang what?

296
00:11:29,650 --> 00:11:30,250
Zhuang...

297
00:11:33,100 --> 00:11:33,830
Keep it down.

298
00:11:34,290 --> 00:11:35,310
Zhuang Zhuang.

299
00:11:35,390 --> 00:11:36,320
Zhuang Zhuang.

300
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:38,980
This is great.

301
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:42,410
We'll soon have a writer

302
00:11:43,030 --> 00:11:44,270
and a singer.

303
00:11:44,790 --> 00:11:46,250
If we get a grandson

304
00:11:46,320 --> 00:11:47,410
who does acting,

305
00:11:47,650 --> 00:11:49,130
well, how lively would it be?

306
00:11:49,130 --> 00:11:50,280
Totally!

307
00:11:50,500 --> 00:11:51,100
Look.

308
00:11:51,600 --> 00:11:54,010
I really like this girl.

309
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:57,740
[Central TV & Radio Tower
(altitude: 405 meters)]

310
00:11:54,080 --> 00:11:55,340
She's perfect.

311
00:11:55,910 --> 00:11:57,370
A perfect match for my son.

312
00:12:22,290 --> 00:12:22,700
Hello?

313
00:12:23,960 --> 00:12:24,910
Hello, Mr. Chu.

314
00:12:26,360 --> 00:12:26,930
Ranran?

315
00:12:28,820 --> 00:12:29,530
Sorry to bother you

316
00:12:29,530 --> 00:12:30,840
over the New Year.

317
00:12:31,720 --> 00:12:32,780
I gave you my number

318
00:12:32,840 --> 00:12:34,530
hoping you would bother me.

319
00:12:35,500 --> 00:12:36,830
But you don't sound like

320
00:12:36,910 --> 00:12:39,100
you're calling to
wish me a happy New Year.

321
00:12:39,100 --> 00:12:40,820
I need a favor from you.

322
00:12:41,360 --> 00:12:41,980
I've already

323
00:12:41,980 --> 00:12:43,270
asked all my friends,

324
00:12:43,320 --> 00:12:44,830
and I'm at my wit's end.

325
00:12:45,100 --> 00:12:46,480
Holding onto this last glimmer of hope,

326
00:12:46,480 --> 00:12:47,500
I wonder if

327
00:12:47,770 --> 00:12:49,430
you have any friends in Huzhou

328
00:12:49,500 --> 00:12:50,190
who can get

329
00:12:50,290 --> 00:12:52,420
a train ticket from Huzhou to Beijing.

330
00:12:52,440 --> 00:12:53,840
I went to the train station to ask,

331
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:54,480
but they said

332
00:12:54,480 --> 00:12:56,590
there are no tickets before the 7th.

333
00:12:56,770 --> 00:12:58,440
You've only been back for a few days,

334
00:12:58,440 --> 00:13:00,270
and you're in such a rush to come back.

335
00:13:00,270 --> 00:13:01,530
Did something happen?

336
00:13:01,650 --> 00:13:02,650
Tell me the truth.

337
00:13:02,770 --> 00:13:03,830
Nothing happened.

338
00:13:05,700 --> 00:13:06,720
I... I just want to

339
00:13:06,740 --> 00:13:08,270
get back to Beijing sooner.

340
00:13:10,460 --> 00:13:12,500
Alright. When do you want to come back?

341
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:14,010
Any time after tomorrow works.

342
00:13:14,010 --> 00:13:15,480
Alright, I'll arrange it.

343
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:16,540
OK.

344
00:13:16,820 --> 00:13:18,250
Thank you. Sorry for the trouble.

345
00:13:18,250 --> 00:13:18,910
No problem.

346
00:13:24,250 --> 00:13:25,010
Is this the standard

347
00:13:25,010 --> 00:13:26,380
for this New Year?

348
00:13:26,500 --> 00:13:27,940
If you like it, I'll make it for you

349
00:13:27,940 --> 00:13:28,860
all year round.

350
00:13:30,120 --> 00:13:30,530
Here.

351
00:13:31,670 --> 00:13:33,200
Almost done. Just one more.

352
00:13:35,030 --> 00:13:35,760
This is nice.

353
00:13:36,790 --> 00:13:37,890
All your favorites.

354
00:13:37,890 --> 00:13:39,650
-Come on. Let's eat.
-Thank you, Mr. Ye.

355
00:13:39,650 --> 00:13:40,210
Eat up.

356
00:13:40,440 --> 00:13:40,770
After we eat,

357
00:13:40,770 --> 00:13:41,700
let's take a walk

358
00:13:41,700 --> 00:13:42,860
in the newly built square.

359
00:13:42,860 --> 00:13:43,260
OK.

360
00:13:43,580 --> 00:13:44,250
Later, wait for me

361
00:13:44,250 --> 00:13:45,510
to come back and we'll go together.

362
00:13:45,510 --> 00:13:46,310
Buy a bit more.

363
00:13:46,340 --> 00:13:46,630
OK.

364
00:13:46,710 --> 00:13:47,860
Where are you going, Mr. Ye?

365
00:13:47,860 --> 00:13:49,120
Don't you love the double-steamed cake

366
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:50,100
from North Street?

367
00:13:50,100 --> 00:13:51,960
I'll have your uncle buy you more.

368
00:13:51,960 --> 00:13:53,290
It might be closed if he goes too late.

369
00:13:53,290 --> 00:13:54,090
And what else?

370
00:13:54,390 --> 00:13:56,120
Buy more of those sponge cakes

371
00:13:56,120 --> 00:13:56,980
and fish cakes too,

372
00:13:56,980 --> 00:13:57,360
so she can

373
00:13:57,360 --> 00:13:58,960
share them with her friends.

374
00:13:59,120 --> 00:13:59,510
Got it.

375
00:13:59,510 --> 00:14:01,040
I still have a few days here.

376
00:14:01,130 --> 00:14:02,270
We can buy them right before I leave.

377
00:14:02,270 --> 00:14:03,200
Let's eat first.

378
00:14:03,220 --> 00:14:04,410
I'm not hungry right now.

379
00:14:04,410 --> 00:14:05,600
They're about to close.

380
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:05,940
Wait.

381
00:14:06,010 --> 00:14:06,770
Eat more.

382
00:14:06,910 --> 00:14:08,640
Don't worry about it. Just eat.

383
00:14:10,100 --> 00:14:11,410
What do you mean, Mom?

384
00:14:11,410 --> 00:14:12,820
Are you trying to kick me out?

385
00:14:12,820 --> 00:14:14,440
I'm so happy when you're home.

386
00:14:14,440 --> 00:14:15,650
Why would I kick you out?

387
00:14:15,650 --> 00:14:16,440
Then why are you rushing Mr. Ye

388
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:17,320
to go buy them?

389
00:14:20,440 --> 00:14:21,860
I know you've been worried sick

390
00:14:21,860 --> 00:14:23,120
these past few days,

391
00:14:23,220 --> 00:14:25,750
afraid that family
would come looking again.

392
00:14:26,030 --> 00:14:26,690
No, I'm not.

393
00:14:27,460 --> 00:14:28,230
I'm afraid them coming

394
00:14:28,230 --> 00:14:29,360
will make you mad again.

395
00:14:29,360 --> 00:14:30,560
And it's the New Year.

396
00:14:30,580 --> 00:14:31,580
If they come to ruin the mood again,

397
00:14:31,580 --> 00:14:32,740
I can still protect you.

398
00:14:32,740 --> 00:14:33,400
They won't.

399
00:14:33,500 --> 00:14:34,500
Ye is here with me.

400
00:14:34,670 --> 00:14:35,670
Do you think the two of us

401
00:14:35,670 --> 00:14:37,030
are afraid of those scoundrels?

402
00:14:37,030 --> 00:14:37,560
Besides,

403
00:14:37,820 --> 00:14:39,520
don't you know my temper?

404
00:14:42,100 --> 00:14:43,160
But no matter what,

405
00:14:43,910 --> 00:14:45,520
it'll be unpleasant.

406
00:14:46,220 --> 00:14:46,870
I don't want

407
00:14:46,870 --> 00:14:48,770
people to gossip about you

408
00:14:49,150 --> 00:14:51,200
when you came back happily
for the New Year.

409
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:51,910
But I...

410
00:14:52,080 --> 00:14:53,300
Don't worry.

411
00:14:53,370 --> 00:14:54,920
Ye and I have our ways.

412
00:14:55,170 --> 00:14:56,290
When you're not home,

413
00:14:56,290 --> 00:14:57,690
I can manage them better.

414
00:14:59,630 --> 00:15:01,430
You mean unleash your fury?

415
00:15:01,510 --> 00:15:03,120
Of course. I'll unleash my fury

416
00:15:03,120 --> 00:15:04,000
and scare them to death.

417
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,600
See if they dare to come back.

418
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:09,390
Come on, let's eat.

419
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:12,000
Eat more of the New Year pudding

420
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:12,620
you love.

421
00:15:22,130 --> 00:15:23,590
Knowing you're in Beijing

422
00:15:23,630 --> 00:15:25,230
with a group of good friends,

423
00:15:25,630 --> 00:15:27,490
I feel relieved to let you go back.

424
00:15:28,240 --> 00:15:29,250
Go back with peace of mind

425
00:15:29,250 --> 00:15:30,910
and focus on learning to sing.

426
00:15:33,200 --> 00:15:34,100
You know what?

427
00:15:34,240 --> 00:15:35,130
The singing tapes

428
00:15:35,130 --> 00:15:36,360
you sent back before,

429
00:15:36,890 --> 00:15:38,310
Ye and I listen to them

430
00:15:38,630 --> 00:15:40,100
several times every day.

431
00:15:41,750 --> 00:15:43,810
Only you guys love listening to them.

432
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:45,860
I sent them for a competition,

433
00:15:45,860 --> 00:15:47,410
but they thought my recording was bad

434
00:15:47,410 --> 00:15:48,870
and asked me to re-record.

435
00:15:48,910 --> 00:15:50,970
Competitions have their standards.

436
00:15:51,080 --> 00:15:52,100
To us,

437
00:15:52,410 --> 00:15:54,210
nothing can ever compare to you.

438
00:15:59,150 --> 00:16:01,320
There's one more important thing.

439
00:16:04,580 --> 00:16:06,960
Say hello to Shengli for us.

440
00:16:08,770 --> 00:16:09,630
When I go back,

441
00:16:09,650 --> 00:16:10,850
I need to investigate

442
00:16:11,130 --> 00:16:11,960
what spell

443
00:16:11,960 --> 00:16:13,220
Xu Shengli cast on you.

444
00:16:14,720 --> 00:16:15,910
A soothing spell.

445
00:16:16,390 --> 00:16:17,530
A soothing spell?

446
00:16:24,500 --> 00:16:24,910
Mom,

447
00:16:25,220 --> 00:16:27,010
how is Dad's old condition?

448
00:16:29,100 --> 00:16:31,100
I asked him, but he wouldn't tell me.

449
00:16:41,050 --> 00:16:41,890
Your dad...

450
00:16:43,750 --> 00:16:44,640
Well,

451
00:16:45,510 --> 00:16:48,360
his old condition flared up a while ago.

452
00:16:48,890 --> 00:16:50,220
He was hospitalized for a few days

453
00:16:50,220 --> 00:16:51,820
but wouldn't let me tell you.

454
00:16:52,240 --> 00:16:52,580
What?

455
00:16:54,390 --> 00:16:56,410
You didn't tell me about such a thing?

456
00:16:56,410 --> 00:16:57,610
Keep your voice down.

457
00:16:58,340 --> 00:16:59,550
He wouldn't let me.

458
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:02,130
He's all better now.

459
00:17:02,750 --> 00:17:04,010
Look, isn't it great

460
00:17:04,010 --> 00:17:05,050
that you're back?

461
00:17:05,290 --> 00:17:06,890
Seeing you makes him so happy

462
00:17:07,200 --> 00:17:09,400
that he feels like he's never been sick.

463
00:17:10,329 --> 00:17:11,530
You are his medicine,

464
00:17:11,680 --> 00:17:12,810
his magic pill.

465
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:13,829
Is he completely cured?

466
00:17:13,829 --> 00:17:14,829
He is. He is.

467
00:17:15,140 --> 00:17:17,829
Don't worry, I'm here.

468
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:22,359
Don't ask him about it.

469
00:17:23,109 --> 00:17:24,380
Just keep it to yourself,

470
00:17:24,380 --> 00:17:25,040
you hear me?

471
00:17:27,030 --> 00:17:28,490
Honey, is the water ready?

472
00:17:30,440 --> 00:17:31,240
Mom, let me go.

473
00:17:32,240 --> 00:17:33,040
-I'll go.
-OK.

474
00:17:41,550 --> 00:17:42,010
No need.

475
00:17:44,570 --> 00:17:45,700
I'll add some water.

476
00:17:51,150 --> 00:17:52,510
Alright, leave it alone.

477
00:17:52,510 --> 00:17:54,110
Let me test the temperature.

478
00:17:58,550 --> 00:17:59,080
Don't...

479
00:18:08,830 --> 00:18:09,560
I have to say,

480
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:12,750
since you came back,

481
00:18:13,030 --> 00:18:14,070
this house has

482
00:18:15,180 --> 00:18:16,700
really livened up a lot.

483
00:18:18,350 --> 00:18:20,330
Alright, then I won't leave for now.

484
00:18:20,330 --> 00:18:22,360
I'll stay at home a bit longer.

485
00:18:22,550 --> 00:18:23,420
Alright.

486
00:18:23,550 --> 00:18:24,570
Don't scare me.

487
00:18:25,310 --> 00:18:26,960
If you want to leave, leave quickly.

488
00:18:26,960 --> 00:18:27,510
Otherwise,

489
00:18:27,510 --> 00:18:28,910
looking at you upsets me.

490
00:18:29,530 --> 00:18:30,590
Go back to Beijing,

491
00:18:30,610 --> 00:18:31,780
and maybe my mood

492
00:18:31,830 --> 00:18:32,630
will improve.

493
00:18:44,920 --> 00:18:45,310
Dad.

494
00:18:46,640 --> 00:18:48,570
If anything happens in the future,

495
00:18:48,700 --> 00:18:49,760
you have to tell me.

496
00:18:51,050 --> 00:18:52,710
My job has no other advantages

497
00:18:53,030 --> 00:18:54,400
except for flexible hours.

498
00:18:54,400 --> 00:18:55,730
I can come back anytime.

499
00:19:00,880 --> 00:19:01,510
In the future,

500
00:19:01,510 --> 00:19:04,310
you absolutely must not
hide things from me again.

501
00:19:14,550 --> 00:19:15,420
We didn't hide anything from you,

502
00:19:15,420 --> 00:19:16,750
and it wasn't a big deal.

503
00:19:18,090 --> 00:19:19,820
It's just that I'm getting old.

504
00:19:20,350 --> 00:19:22,280
Illness strikes like a landslide,

505
00:19:22,700 --> 00:19:23,560
and recovery is

506
00:19:24,790 --> 00:19:26,120
as slow as reeling silk.

507
00:19:28,180 --> 00:19:30,310
During those few days in the hospital,

508
00:19:31,720 --> 00:19:33,240
lying on that bed,

509
00:19:34,830 --> 00:19:36,010
I really missed you.

510
00:19:38,720 --> 00:19:39,720
A good man

511
00:19:41,440 --> 00:19:43,440
should go out and explore the world.

512
00:19:44,880 --> 00:19:45,810
If we always

513
00:19:45,830 --> 00:19:47,030
kept you tied to us,

514
00:19:47,680 --> 00:19:49,220
you would never grow up

515
00:19:49,720 --> 00:19:51,320
and can't spread your wings.

516
00:19:53,850 --> 00:19:55,290
That's the logic.

517
00:19:56,590 --> 00:19:58,770
But what I fear the most

518
00:20:00,700 --> 00:20:02,640
is that you'll suffer out there.

519
00:20:07,960 --> 00:20:09,620
Both ends of the carrying pole

520
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:11,060
are equally heavy.

521
00:20:13,480 --> 00:20:14,820
Your mother and I

522
00:20:15,980 --> 00:20:16,920
don't know

523
00:20:18,090 --> 00:20:19,620
whether we should let you go

524
00:20:21,640 --> 00:20:23,240
or make you stay.

525
00:20:31,570 --> 00:20:31,960
Dad.

526
00:20:32,920 --> 00:20:33,980
In our line of work,

527
00:20:35,230 --> 00:20:36,360
only in Beijing

528
00:20:36,900 --> 00:20:38,300
can we truly find a stage.

529
00:20:40,110 --> 00:20:41,040
Beijing is huge,

530
00:20:41,850 --> 00:20:42,710
full of talents

531
00:20:43,530 --> 00:20:44,660
and opportunities.

532
00:20:49,680 --> 00:20:51,480
I want to try for another 2 years.

533
00:20:53,090 --> 00:20:55,220
If I still can't make a name for myself,

534
00:20:56,420 --> 00:20:57,460
I'll give up.

535
00:20:58,710 --> 00:21:00,110
Make a name for yourself?

536
00:21:04,900 --> 00:21:05,690
Tell me,

537
00:21:08,660 --> 00:21:09,790
what does that mean?

538
00:21:11,850 --> 00:21:13,030
I must at least make sure you and Mom

539
00:21:13,030 --> 00:21:14,610
are well fed and properly clothed,

540
00:21:14,610 --> 00:21:16,090
without worries about money.

541
00:21:16,090 --> 00:21:16,640
What?

542
00:21:17,850 --> 00:21:18,610
Are we not well fed

543
00:21:18,610 --> 00:21:20,410
and properly clothed right now?

544
00:21:23,010 --> 00:21:24,700
T-Then, at least...

545
00:21:26,110 --> 00:21:27,710
I have to make an impression.

546
00:21:27,790 --> 00:21:29,240
I have to let people see your son...

547
00:21:29,240 --> 00:21:30,610
your son on TV.

548
00:21:32,110 --> 00:21:34,050
Those are your own pursuits.

549
00:21:34,480 --> 00:21:35,740
There's no end to that.

550
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:44,000
Do you think your mom and I...

551
00:21:46,850 --> 00:21:47,780
are successful?

552
00:21:47,900 --> 00:21:49,630
Of course you are. Need you ask?

553
00:21:51,110 --> 00:21:52,840
Raising a piece of work like me,

554
00:21:53,480 --> 00:21:55,140
that sure takes a lot of skill.

555
00:21:55,240 --> 00:21:55,770
Alright.

556
00:21:57,240 --> 00:21:58,940
As long as you know that.

557
00:22:01,940 --> 00:22:03,920
Actually, every parent

558
00:22:05,070 --> 00:22:07,200
hopes for the best for their children.

559
00:22:09,160 --> 00:22:11,700
But whether you're successful

560
00:22:11,700 --> 00:22:13,180
or capable,

561
00:22:14,350 --> 00:22:15,750
that's just how

562
00:22:15,830 --> 00:22:17,570
outsiders measure you.

563
00:22:18,850 --> 00:22:19,900
As parents,

564
00:22:22,250 --> 00:22:23,220
we only hope that

565
00:22:25,460 --> 00:22:26,940
you are happy in your heart

566
00:22:28,110 --> 00:22:29,440
and strong in your body!

567
00:22:32,240 --> 00:22:33,760
If you can fly high,

568
00:22:35,180 --> 00:22:36,750
we'll be happy for you.

569
00:22:39,290 --> 00:22:42,090
When you're tired of flying
and can't fly anymore,

570
00:22:42,290 --> 00:22:42,980
come back.

571
00:22:44,030 --> 00:22:44,920
In this house,

572
00:22:45,570 --> 00:22:47,750
there will always be a bed for you.

573
00:22:52,700 --> 00:22:54,160
But you have to understand

574
00:22:54,590 --> 00:22:56,120
your parents' intentions.

575
00:22:58,480 --> 00:22:59,830
You have to live up...

576
00:23:03,030 --> 00:23:04,270
to your own choices.

577
00:23:08,880 --> 00:23:10,090
Even if one day

578
00:23:11,570 --> 00:23:12,570
you become a perfectly

579
00:23:12,570 --> 00:23:13,740
ordinary person,

580
00:23:15,460 --> 00:23:17,920
you must still live
with your head held high.

581
00:23:20,700 --> 00:23:22,160
Does what I say make sense?

582
00:23:25,160 --> 00:23:25,770
Yes.

583
00:23:26,770 --> 00:23:29,470
My dad is truly a visionary.

584
00:23:29,980 --> 00:23:31,780
Your perspective is top-notch.

585
00:23:33,110 --> 00:23:36,140
I think you need another beating.

586
00:23:44,140 --> 00:23:45,000
Add some water.

587
00:23:45,460 --> 00:23:46,390
Enough.

588
00:23:47,420 --> 00:23:47,810
OK.

589
00:23:57,880 --> 00:23:58,920
What big buns!

590
00:24:00,660 --> 00:24:01,090
Chief.

591
00:24:01,850 --> 00:24:02,510
Please come in.

592
00:24:02,510 --> 00:24:03,070
No, no.

593
00:24:03,790 --> 00:24:05,020
I have things to do.

594
00:24:05,440 --> 00:24:05,850
Come.

595
00:24:06,110 --> 00:24:07,240
Have a seat for a bit.

596
00:24:07,750 --> 00:24:08,720
Where's the young man?

597
00:24:08,720 --> 00:24:10,050
He's right in this room.

598
00:24:11,920 --> 00:24:13,010
I haven't seen him.

599
00:24:13,980 --> 00:24:15,810
I wonder how

600
00:24:15,960 --> 00:24:17,500
he's doing in Beijing now.

601
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:21,730
On the first day of the New Year,

602
00:24:22,010 --> 00:24:23,570
didn't he go pay you a visit?

603
00:24:24,050 --> 00:24:25,090
I told him

604
00:24:25,960 --> 00:24:27,890
to visit you first for the New Year.

605
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:30,550
Really?

606
00:24:32,270 --> 00:24:33,200
I didn't see him.

607
00:24:33,290 --> 00:24:33,960
Cao Ye!

608
00:24:34,720 --> 00:24:35,490
Come here!

609
00:24:36,160 --> 00:24:37,160
This kid of mine

610
00:24:37,720 --> 00:24:38,720
stays up all night

611
00:24:39,240 --> 00:24:41,100
and sleeps like a log all morning.

612
00:24:41,110 --> 00:24:42,110
He's a total mess.

613
00:24:43,680 --> 00:24:44,480
Hello, Chief.

614
00:24:45,900 --> 00:24:47,940
Look at you, yawning all the time.

615
00:24:49,460 --> 00:24:49,900
Cao.

616
00:24:51,480 --> 00:24:53,980
I have a favor to ask.

617
00:24:54,830 --> 00:24:55,770
Our township is

618
00:24:55,960 --> 00:24:57,760
going to hold a Lantern Festival

619
00:24:57,790 --> 00:24:59,320
on the 15th.

620
00:24:59,700 --> 00:25:00,500
Every village

621
00:25:01,030 --> 00:25:02,360
is competing to host it.

622
00:25:02,980 --> 00:25:04,910
Our village has priority

623
00:25:05,590 --> 00:25:06,990
because of you.

624
00:25:07,480 --> 00:25:08,550
I'd like to ask you

625
00:25:08,920 --> 00:25:10,570
to paint on

626
00:25:11,010 --> 00:25:11,810
100 lanterns.

627
00:25:17,850 --> 00:25:18,710
What do you say?

628
00:25:26,290 --> 00:25:26,830
Why...

629
00:25:27,140 --> 00:25:28,350
Why are you eating?

630
00:25:29,550 --> 00:25:30,940
Answer him, will you?

631
00:25:35,570 --> 00:25:36,810
The young man is successful now,

632
00:25:36,810 --> 00:25:38,870
and looks down on our little village.

633
00:25:39,610 --> 00:25:40,610
It's the New Year.

634
00:25:42,070 --> 00:25:43,590
I won't disturb you two.

635
00:25:44,380 --> 00:25:45,440
I'll take my leave.

636
00:25:45,720 --> 00:25:46,830
Don't go, Chief!

637
00:25:48,250 --> 00:25:49,220
Take some steamed buns with you.

638
00:25:49,220 --> 00:25:50,770
-I'm leaving. Bye.
-Let me get you some.

639
00:25:50,770 --> 00:25:52,100
Take some buns with you.

640
00:26:13,880 --> 00:26:15,610
On the first day of the New Year,

641
00:26:16,140 --> 00:26:17,310
I told you to go first to

642
00:26:17,310 --> 00:26:19,420
the village chief's house to greet him.

643
00:26:19,420 --> 00:26:20,600
Why didn't you go?

644
00:26:20,750 --> 00:26:21,720
There were too many people.

645
00:26:21,720 --> 00:26:23,230
I couldn't squeeze in.

646
00:26:24,140 --> 00:26:25,740
Then you should have waited.

647
00:26:26,000 --> 00:26:27,770
How could I wait? Until when?

648
00:26:28,030 --> 00:26:28,420
Dad,

649
00:26:29,400 --> 00:26:30,000
you can't always

650
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:31,530
live on the whims of others.

651
00:26:40,680 --> 00:26:41,570
When

652
00:26:42,460 --> 00:26:44,030
you've become a big shot,

653
00:26:44,920 --> 00:26:46,270
then I won't have to.

654
00:26:46,750 --> 00:26:48,160
It's only a matter of time.

655
00:26:48,160 --> 00:26:49,460
What did the chief ask me to do?

656
00:26:49,460 --> 00:26:50,740
To paint lanterns.

657
00:26:50,980 --> 00:26:52,380
Painting lanterns, Dad!

658
00:26:52,810 --> 00:26:54,410
That's a waste of my talents.

659
00:26:54,500 --> 00:26:56,440
That's using a sledgehammer
to crack a nut.

660
00:26:56,440 --> 00:26:57,290
Impossible.

661
00:27:02,140 --> 00:27:02,790
Got it.

662
00:27:20,610 --> 00:27:22,010
Little Northeasterner!

663
00:27:22,480 --> 00:27:23,180
Welcome the guest.

664
00:27:23,180 --> 00:27:24,040
Zhuang Zhuang,

665
00:27:24,330 --> 00:27:25,810
why are you back so early?

666
00:27:25,980 --> 00:27:27,440
I came back for something.

667
00:27:28,200 --> 00:27:28,610
Here,

668
00:27:29,510 --> 00:27:30,550
Happy New Year.

669
00:27:30,830 --> 00:27:31,960
I'm a bit embarrassed.

670
00:27:31,960 --> 00:27:33,560
Well, I won't be polite then.

671
00:27:33,700 --> 00:27:34,720
No need to be polite.

672
00:27:34,720 --> 00:27:35,770
Let's eat together tonight.

673
00:27:35,770 --> 00:27:36,840
Don't eat alone.

674
00:27:37,000 --> 00:27:37,830
Sure.

675
00:27:37,960 --> 00:27:38,960
Is anyone back?

676
00:27:39,090 --> 00:27:39,920
The New Year's just begun.

677
00:27:39,920 --> 00:27:40,850
No one's back yet.

678
00:27:40,850 --> 00:27:41,880
You should go down quickly.

679
00:27:41,880 --> 00:27:42,850
You'll freeze here. Go now.

680
00:27:42,850 --> 00:27:43,220
OK.

681
00:27:44,090 --> 00:27:45,290
The lanterns look nice.

682
00:27:45,290 --> 00:27:46,060
Right?

683
00:28:02,590 --> 00:28:03,450
Zhuang Zhuang?

684
00:28:03,790 --> 00:28:04,540
You're back.

685
00:28:04,570 --> 00:28:05,550
You guys are back too.

686
00:28:05,550 --> 00:28:07,010
Zhuang Zhuang, thank you.

687
00:28:07,770 --> 00:28:09,230
Thanks for the dumplings.

688
00:28:10,170 --> 00:28:11,670
[Save electricity]

689
00:28:15,420 --> 00:28:15,960
Come on.

690
00:28:16,400 --> 00:28:19,990
[Save electricity]

691
00:28:31,420 --> 00:28:32,280
It's still hot.

692
00:28:33,050 --> 00:28:33,850
I'll go put my things down.

693
00:28:33,850 --> 00:28:34,980
OK, hurry up.

694
00:28:39,880 --> 00:28:40,880
Ranran.

695
00:28:41,420 --> 00:28:42,140
Ranran!

696
00:28:44,140 --> 00:28:44,980
Ranran?

697
00:28:45,680 --> 00:28:46,500
What's wrong with you,

698
00:28:46,500 --> 00:28:47,700
dawdling like this?

699
00:28:50,460 --> 00:28:51,550
Seriously.

700
00:28:52,740 --> 00:28:54,920
Who are you pulling that long face for?

701
00:28:55,590 --> 00:28:56,030
We agreed

702
00:28:56,030 --> 00:28:57,420
to meet Mr. Liu today.

703
00:28:57,460 --> 00:28:58,790
Why didn't you dress up?

704
00:28:59,350 --> 00:29:02,000
-You're going to embarrass me.
-To hell with Mr. Liu.

705
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:03,600
Mr. Liu is a big boss!

706
00:29:04,380 --> 00:29:05,110
This brat...

707
00:29:05,760 --> 00:29:07,090
Happy New Year, Ranran.

708
00:29:08,110 --> 00:29:09,010
Mr. Chu?

709
00:29:10,510 --> 00:29:10,910
You...

710
00:29:12,480 --> 00:29:13,280
This is...

711
00:29:13,550 --> 00:29:14,640
This is my mother.

712
00:29:15,710 --> 00:29:17,480
Happy New Year, Ma'am.

713
00:29:17,900 --> 00:29:18,860
Hello, hello.

714
00:29:18,960 --> 00:29:19,660
Who are you?

715
00:29:19,680 --> 00:29:21,280
This is Mr. Chu from Beijing.

716
00:29:21,480 --> 00:29:22,430
From Beijing?

717
00:29:23,030 --> 00:29:24,740
I've always wanted to pay you a visit,

718
00:29:24,740 --> 00:29:25,850
but I didn't have the time.

719
00:29:25,850 --> 00:29:26,480
It's the New Year,

720
00:29:26,480 --> 00:29:27,550
so I brought you some gifts.

721
00:29:27,550 --> 00:29:28,830
Just a token of my appreciation.

722
00:29:28,830 --> 00:29:30,160
You even brought gifts?

723
00:29:30,250 --> 00:29:31,380
You shouldn't have.

724
00:29:31,810 --> 00:29:32,990
Put them in the house.

725
00:29:32,990 --> 00:29:33,740
Come on.

726
00:29:37,960 --> 00:29:41,100
It's so hard to get train tickets
during the New Year.

727
00:29:41,330 --> 00:29:42,460
How did you get here?

728
00:29:42,530 --> 00:29:43,480
I flew here.

729
00:29:43,960 --> 00:29:45,730
How did you know

730
00:29:45,790 --> 00:29:46,940
my hometown address?

731
00:29:46,940 --> 00:29:47,700
Cui has it.

732
00:29:47,850 --> 00:29:48,950
I got it from him.

733
00:29:51,030 --> 00:29:52,430
Where are you guys going?

734
00:29:52,550 --> 00:29:54,400
My mom and I are going to eat

735
00:29:54,480 --> 00:29:55,460
with her friend.

736
00:29:57,610 --> 00:29:58,810
Why don't you join us?

737
00:29:59,510 --> 00:30:00,920
Sure, I'll go with you.

738
00:30:01,960 --> 00:30:03,620
A dinner fraught with danger?

739
00:30:19,310 --> 00:30:20,160
Shut up.

740
00:30:22,900 --> 00:30:23,530
Get lost.

741
00:30:23,810 --> 00:30:24,740
What do you mean?

742
00:30:25,160 --> 00:30:26,080
Are you deaf?

743
00:30:26,140 --> 00:30:27,340
I said, "Put it down!"

744
00:30:29,790 --> 00:30:30,680
What do you mean?

745
00:30:30,680 --> 00:30:31,710
What do you mean?

746
00:30:32,310 --> 00:30:33,260
Want to fight?

747
00:30:33,350 --> 00:30:34,410
Let's have a go.

748
00:30:34,880 --> 00:30:35,660
Shirts off?

749
00:30:38,270 --> 00:30:38,930
Come on.

750
00:30:39,010 --> 00:30:39,500
Come on.

751
00:30:39,500 --> 00:30:40,430
Let's do it.

752
00:30:40,500 --> 00:30:41,270
Come on!

753
00:30:43,030 --> 00:30:44,070
Jun!

754
00:30:44,070 --> 00:30:45,930
Liangliang, I missed you so much.

755
00:30:47,610 --> 00:30:48,980
I missed you too, Jun.

756
00:30:54,300 --> 00:30:56,050
Why are you still watching
the Spring Festival Gala?

757
00:30:56,050 --> 00:30:57,400
On New Year's Eve, I was busy

758
00:30:57,400 --> 00:30:59,600
drinking and chatting with my parents.

759
00:31:00,200 --> 00:31:01,770
I didn't really watch the Gala.

760
00:31:01,770 --> 00:31:03,170
I heard it's really good.

761
00:31:03,400 --> 00:31:04,460
The dumplings are good too.

762
00:31:04,460 --> 00:31:05,660
Did you make them all?

763
00:31:05,900 --> 00:31:06,830
My mom made them.

764
00:31:07,530 --> 00:31:08,620
My mom even said

765
00:31:09,090 --> 00:31:10,750
I should bring all of this

766
00:31:10,830 --> 00:31:12,490
for Miss Zhuang Zhuang to try.

767
00:31:18,790 --> 00:31:19,400
Try this.

768
00:31:21,510 --> 00:31:22,940
Hairtail. It's really good.

769
00:31:22,940 --> 00:31:24,500
It tastes better freshly made.

770
00:31:24,500 --> 00:31:25,420
If you have a chance,

771
00:31:25,420 --> 00:31:26,290
come visit my hometown.

772
00:31:26,290 --> 00:31:28,020
I'll have my mom make it for you.

773
00:31:36,960 --> 00:31:37,440
Yummy.

774
00:31:38,510 --> 00:31:39,510
Have another one.

775
00:31:39,530 --> 00:31:41,060
I'll finish this one first.

776
00:31:41,810 --> 00:31:42,330
OK.

777
00:31:49,500 --> 00:31:51,830
Eating something hot really warmed me up.

778
00:31:52,160 --> 00:31:53,360
Coming back from my parents',

779
00:31:53,360 --> 00:31:55,030
this basement feels even colder.

780
00:31:55,030 --> 00:31:55,960
Everyone's home for the New Year.

781
00:31:55,960 --> 00:31:57,330
I guess Little Northeasterner's boiler

782
00:31:57,330 --> 00:31:58,660
wasn't fired up enough.

783
00:32:02,460 --> 00:32:03,920
Have a glass of wine to warm up.

784
00:32:03,920 --> 00:32:04,330
Come.

785
00:32:05,660 --> 00:32:07,520
-Happy New Year!
-Happy New Year!

786
00:32:15,680 --> 00:32:17,140
You can stay here tonight.

787
00:32:17,750 --> 00:32:19,410
I'll change the water in this.

788
00:32:59,900 --> 00:33:01,270
Here, try this.

789
00:33:04,050 --> 00:33:04,710
Feeling OK?

790
00:33:05,090 --> 00:33:05,820
Much better.

791
00:33:07,240 --> 00:33:08,820
Put the blanket on.

792
00:33:09,000 --> 00:33:10,200
It's warmer this way.

793
00:33:17,070 --> 00:33:17,510
Here.

794
00:33:38,680 --> 00:33:39,780
My place is warm.

795
00:33:39,980 --> 00:33:41,200
You stay here tonight.

796
00:33:41,200 --> 00:33:42,200
I'll grab two more blankets

797
00:33:42,200 --> 00:33:43,460
and stay in your place.

798
00:33:58,660 --> 00:33:59,420
Are you cold?

799
00:34:00,010 --> 00:34:00,670
I'm fine.

800
00:34:01,270 --> 00:34:02,650
Then how about we share?

801
00:34:02,940 --> 00:34:04,140
It's warmer this way.

802
00:34:26,710 --> 00:34:27,710
Are you that cold?

803
00:34:28,130 --> 00:34:28,860
I'm not cold.

804
00:35:07,510 --> 00:35:08,730
It's so cold today.

805
00:35:12,170 --> 00:35:13,400
Sorry to intrude.

806
00:35:15,430 --> 00:35:16,280
I-I-I...

807
00:35:16,440 --> 00:35:17,090
No, no.

808
00:35:17,210 --> 00:35:17,960
You aren't intruding.

809
00:35:17,960 --> 00:35:19,010
Is it inconvenient?

810
00:35:19,010 --> 00:35:19,880
No, it's not!

811
00:35:20,610 --> 00:35:22,880
Then... Please continue.

812
00:35:25,440 --> 00:35:25,960
Well,

813
00:35:26,570 --> 00:35:27,840
let me introduce you

814
00:35:28,050 --> 00:35:28,880
to a new guest.

815
00:35:29,300 --> 00:35:29,870
Jun!

816
00:35:32,840 --> 00:35:33,320
Hello?

817
00:35:35,480 --> 00:35:36,610
OK, OK.

818
00:35:37,230 --> 00:35:38,760
The signal's bad.

819
00:35:38,840 --> 00:35:40,400
T-Talk to you later.

820
00:35:40,860 --> 00:35:41,860
This cell phone is

821
00:35:41,960 --> 00:35:43,070
so expensive but has bad signal.

822
00:35:43,070 --> 00:35:44,690
Yes, we are half underground here.

823
00:35:44,690 --> 00:35:45,230
Right.

824
00:35:46,780 --> 00:35:47,860
The environment here is not bad.

825
00:35:47,860 --> 00:35:48,660
A big villa.

826
00:35:48,760 --> 00:35:49,730
It's quite cozy.

827
00:35:50,210 --> 00:35:51,550
Let me introduce—

828
00:35:51,920 --> 00:35:52,960
this is Xu Shengli,

829
00:35:52,960 --> 00:35:53,800
a famous writer.

830
00:35:53,800 --> 00:35:54,360
Nice to meet you.

831
00:35:54,360 --> 00:35:55,690
Cultured, so cultured.

832
00:35:55,800 --> 00:35:56,480
Zhuang Zhuang,

833
00:35:56,480 --> 00:35:57,410
a famous singer.

834
00:35:57,480 --> 00:35:58,810
Talented, so talented!

835
00:36:02,130 --> 00:36:03,260
Ma Xiaojun.

836
00:36:03,510 --> 00:36:05,500
Just call him Jun.
He's my childhood friend.

837
00:36:05,500 --> 00:36:07,000
He plays the saxophone better than me.

838
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:07,440
Jun.

839
00:36:07,570 --> 00:36:08,130
Jun.

840
00:36:08,150 --> 00:36:08,800
You flatter me.

841
00:36:08,800 --> 00:36:09,900
That's all in the past.

842
00:36:09,900 --> 00:36:11,300
Now I mainly do business.

843
00:36:12,130 --> 00:36:13,570
Let's not just stand here.

844
00:36:13,570 --> 00:36:14,630
Let's sit down and talk.

845
00:36:14,630 --> 00:36:15,360
Sit, sit.

846
00:36:15,590 --> 00:36:16,190
Let's sit.

847
00:36:16,260 --> 00:36:17,390
Having dinner, huh?

848
00:36:17,630 --> 00:36:18,840
Is this convenient?

849
00:36:18,840 --> 00:36:19,730
Totally.

850
00:36:19,730 --> 00:36:21,190
-Sit, Jun.
-It's convenient, yeah?

851
00:36:21,190 --> 00:36:22,030
Just in time. I haven't eaten.

852
00:36:22,030 --> 00:36:23,380
Let's set up another table. Is this OK?

853
00:36:23,380 --> 00:36:24,280
It's OK. This is fine.

854
00:36:24,280 --> 00:36:25,260
Very cozy.

855
00:36:25,320 --> 00:36:26,150
Y-You two,

856
00:36:26,170 --> 00:36:27,640
just sit where you were.

857
00:36:27,710 --> 00:36:29,310
Close the door. It's drafty.

858
00:36:29,960 --> 00:36:30,920
Come on, sit.

859
00:36:35,340 --> 00:36:36,050
Mr. Liu!

860
00:36:37,300 --> 00:36:37,760
Ranran.

861
00:36:37,900 --> 00:36:38,360
Hello.

862
00:36:38,590 --> 00:36:40,400
Old Classmate, do you still remember me?

863
00:36:40,400 --> 00:36:40,930
She does!

864
00:36:40,960 --> 00:36:43,290
You were in first grade
when I was in sixth.

865
00:36:43,710 --> 00:36:44,630
You got even prettier!

866
00:36:44,630 --> 00:36:44,960
Yeah.

867
00:36:44,980 --> 00:36:45,920
Quickly! Have a seat!

868
00:36:45,920 --> 00:36:46,980
Come, Ranran, sit.

869
00:36:47,860 --> 00:36:49,110
It's fine. Make yourself comfortable.

870
00:36:49,110 --> 00:36:50,380
OK, I'll sit here.

871
00:36:50,460 --> 00:36:51,210
Come on.

872
00:36:51,380 --> 00:36:53,710
Eat while it's hot. The food just arrived.

873
00:36:54,590 --> 00:36:55,420
And this is...

874
00:36:56,320 --> 00:36:56,960
He is...

875
00:36:57,710 --> 00:36:58,640
I'm Chu Caiyuan.

876
00:36:59,760 --> 00:37:00,760
I'm Liu Xiangcai.

877
00:37:01,500 --> 00:37:03,780
What a coincidence that
your name also has a "cai" in it.

878
00:37:03,780 --> 00:37:04,980
Is it the character for wealth,

879
00:37:04,980 --> 00:37:06,180
or the one for talent?

880
00:37:06,190 --> 00:37:07,250
The one for talent.

881
00:37:07,320 --> 00:37:09,190
Mine is the one for wealth!

882
00:37:11,010 --> 00:37:12,690
It's a common name
given by my grandfather,

883
00:37:12,690 --> 00:37:14,290
so I didn't dare to change it.

884
00:37:14,480 --> 00:37:16,500
But fortunately,
borrowing from the old man's luck,

885
00:37:16,500 --> 00:37:18,210
this name has brought me prosperity.

886
00:37:18,210 --> 00:37:19,350
These years,

887
00:37:19,880 --> 00:37:21,360
I only have wealth.

888
00:37:23,230 --> 00:37:24,830
Having money is a good thing.

889
00:37:24,960 --> 00:37:26,560
Why say you only have wealth?

890
00:37:26,780 --> 00:37:28,170
Because that's all I have left.

891
00:37:28,170 --> 00:37:30,280
Although Mr. Liu is young,

892
00:37:30,280 --> 00:37:32,650
he runs a big business.

893
00:37:34,320 --> 00:37:35,730
What kind of business is it?

894
00:37:35,730 --> 00:37:36,730
Well, bras.

895
00:37:37,860 --> 00:37:39,260
That is, undergarments.

896
00:37:39,980 --> 00:37:40,610
Let me tell you,

897
00:37:40,610 --> 00:37:42,880
the profit margin for bras is really good.

898
00:37:42,880 --> 00:37:44,080
My family's business

899
00:37:44,090 --> 00:37:44,900
started as a small factory

900
00:37:44,900 --> 00:37:45,940
with just over 20 people.

901
00:37:45,940 --> 00:37:46,660
With

902
00:37:47,090 --> 00:37:49,080
15,000 pieces sold per month

903
00:37:49,280 --> 00:37:51,750
and an annual turnover of about a million,

904
00:37:51,960 --> 00:37:54,130
the net profit is this much.

905
00:37:56,900 --> 00:37:58,340
Now we've made it big.

906
00:37:58,590 --> 00:37:59,440
Now, places like

907
00:37:59,440 --> 00:38:00,960
Baima Market in Guangzhou

908
00:38:00,980 --> 00:38:02,320
and Hanzheng Street in Wuhan

909
00:38:02,320 --> 00:38:03,580
all sell our products.

910
00:38:04,460 --> 00:38:06,000
Actually, bras are just

911
00:38:06,000 --> 00:38:07,060
synthetic fibers.

912
00:38:07,190 --> 00:38:08,990
The cost price is only a few yuan.

913
00:38:10,070 --> 00:38:11,900
After I took over,
I immediately improved it.

914
00:38:11,900 --> 00:38:13,090
I told them, "Let me tell you,

915
00:38:13,090 --> 00:38:14,120
you need to change

916
00:38:14,150 --> 00:38:15,010
the stuffing."

917
00:38:15,090 --> 00:38:15,690
Why?

918
00:38:16,840 --> 00:38:18,940
W-Well, the shape of the breast,

919
00:38:19,000 --> 00:38:20,530
you know, it's very hard...

920
00:38:21,230 --> 00:38:21,840
Mr. Liu,

921
00:38:22,500 --> 00:38:24,480
production details shouldn't be revealed.

922
00:38:24,480 --> 00:38:25,740
Keep it confidential.

923
00:38:30,710 --> 00:38:32,910
Mr. Chu, what kind of business do you do?

924
00:38:33,760 --> 00:38:34,690
A bit of everything.

925
00:38:34,690 --> 00:38:36,550
So you don't have a main business.

926
00:38:37,010 --> 00:38:39,610
What business are you
discussing on this trip?

927
00:38:39,940 --> 00:38:40,420
Silk.

928
00:38:40,670 --> 00:38:41,780
The mogul of silk

929
00:38:41,820 --> 00:38:43,140
is Mr. Hu from Hongye.

930
00:38:43,260 --> 00:38:44,120
Do you know him?

931
00:38:46,630 --> 00:38:48,590
Mr. Hu and I are really tight.

932
00:38:48,940 --> 00:38:50,000
I call him Uncle Hu.

933
00:38:50,270 --> 00:38:54,000
-Come here. Room 666.
-I always get their silk. He ought to thank me.

934
00:38:56,650 --> 00:38:57,910
Mr. Chu, your watch...

935
00:38:59,550 --> 00:39:00,280
It's decent.

936
00:39:00,590 --> 00:39:01,650
It keeps good time.

937
00:39:02,000 --> 00:39:03,400
Mr. Liu, you have a guest.

938
00:39:03,730 --> 00:39:04,390
Let them in.

939
00:39:06,760 --> 00:39:07,650
Mr. Chu.

940
00:39:09,690 --> 00:39:10,210
Mr. Hu!

941
00:39:14,360 --> 00:39:15,620
How did you end up here?

942
00:39:16,730 --> 00:39:17,530
That's Mr. Hu.

943
00:39:19,070 --> 00:39:20,360
I'm here to spend some time

944
00:39:20,360 --> 00:39:21,230
with a few friends.

945
00:39:21,230 --> 00:39:22,400
The Silk King!

946
00:39:22,800 --> 00:39:24,090
We threw a welcome dinner

947
00:39:24,090 --> 00:39:25,130
just for you, our big investor,

948
00:39:25,130 --> 00:39:26,610
and we almost lost you.

949
00:39:27,630 --> 00:39:28,750
Mr. Hu!

950
00:39:33,260 --> 00:39:34,090
Who is this?

951
00:39:35,980 --> 00:39:37,150
Let me introduce you.

952
00:39:37,150 --> 00:39:38,340
This is my friend from Beijing,

953
00:39:38,340 --> 00:39:40,200
the famous actress, Shen Ranran.

954
00:39:40,440 --> 00:39:40,960
Hello.

955
00:39:41,210 --> 00:39:41,730
Hello.

956
00:39:42,400 --> 00:39:43,470
This is her mother.

957
00:39:43,980 --> 00:39:44,690
Hello, hello!

958
00:39:44,690 --> 00:39:45,340
Hello.

959
00:39:45,380 --> 00:39:46,980
The Silk King, Hu Xianghong.

960
00:39:48,130 --> 00:39:49,210
I don't need to introduce this one.

961
00:39:49,210 --> 00:39:49,710
This young man

962
00:39:49,710 --> 00:39:51,170
was just talking about you.

963
00:39:51,170 --> 00:39:51,710
Uncle Hu.

964
00:39:51,880 --> 00:39:53,160
I'm Liu Xiangcai.

965
00:39:56,320 --> 00:39:57,340
W-What cai?

966
00:39:57,900 --> 00:39:59,260
It doesn't matter.

967
00:39:59,340 --> 00:40:00,150
Come, sit.

968
00:40:00,150 --> 00:40:01,570
-Yeah, sit here!
-No, thanks.

969
00:40:01,570 --> 00:40:02,940
My dear honored guest,

970
00:40:02,940 --> 00:40:04,670
would you please come back with me?

971
00:40:04,670 --> 00:40:05,730
Come on, Mr. Chu.

972
00:40:05,780 --> 00:40:07,300
OK, I'll go over for a bit.

973
00:40:07,300 --> 00:40:08,800
They are all waiting for you.

974
00:40:08,800 --> 00:40:10,660
Take your time and enjoy the food.

975
00:40:16,690 --> 00:40:17,840
Mr. Chu, come on now.

976
00:40:18,820 --> 00:40:20,320
Everyone is waiting for you.

977
00:40:20,320 --> 00:40:22,320
We were looking for you everywhere.

978
00:40:25,590 --> 00:40:26,860
Just Mr. Chu's watch

979
00:40:28,400 --> 00:40:30,200
is worth a whole factory of mine.

980
00:40:34,530 --> 00:40:35,070
What?

981
00:40:36,940 --> 00:40:38,070
How much do you need?

982
00:40:38,650 --> 00:40:39,700
1,000 yuan?

983
00:40:39,900 --> 00:40:40,960
That's too little!

984
00:40:40,960 --> 00:40:41,360
I-It's

985
00:40:41,500 --> 00:40:43,050
not even enough for my phone bill!

986
00:40:43,050 --> 00:40:43,500
Eat while it's hot.

987
00:40:43,500 --> 00:40:44,780
When do you need it? In 3 days?

988
00:40:44,780 --> 00:40:45,380
OK, no problem!

989
00:40:45,380 --> 00:40:47,910
You Beijingers don't go home
for the New Year?

990
00:40:48,420 --> 00:40:50,120
I bought him out.

991
00:40:51,920 --> 00:40:52,690
What do you mean?

992
00:40:52,690 --> 00:40:53,840
I'll call you back later.

993
00:40:53,840 --> 00:40:54,630
I'm eating!

994
00:40:57,710 --> 00:40:58,590
Jun, hurry and eat.

995
00:40:58,590 --> 00:40:59,670
-Eat while it's hot.
-It's getting cold.

996
00:40:59,670 --> 00:41:00,340
Take this 50 yuan

997
00:41:00,340 --> 00:41:01,280
as your pocket money.

998
00:41:01,280 --> 00:41:02,010
Keep it.

999
00:41:02,670 --> 00:41:04,320
I came back to find you this time,

1000
00:41:04,320 --> 00:41:04,920
mainly

1001
00:41:05,550 --> 00:41:07,190
to ask if you want to work with me.

1002
00:41:07,190 --> 00:41:09,650
I'll take you to
do big things; great things.

1003
00:41:09,840 --> 00:41:11,840
This is my current business card.

1004
00:41:12,300 --> 00:41:12,690
Here.

1005
00:41:13,380 --> 00:41:13,820
Here.

1006
00:41:14,380 --> 00:41:14,980
Thank you.

1007
00:41:16,940 --> 00:41:17,760
Keep it safe.

1008
00:41:17,780 --> 00:41:19,710
Don't always just throw them away.

1009
00:41:19,840 --> 00:41:21,430
I've kept every card

1010
00:41:21,500 --> 00:41:22,410
you gave me.

1011
00:41:22,590 --> 00:41:23,720
I saved them for you.

1012
00:41:24,300 --> 00:41:25,160
So thoughtful?

1013
00:41:28,400 --> 00:41:29,420
Eat slowly. It's hot.

1014
00:41:29,420 --> 00:41:30,750
-It's fine.
-Look, Jun.

1015
00:41:31,860 --> 00:41:33,660
How many cards have you given me?

1016
00:41:36,690 --> 00:41:38,150
Here, take a look, you two.

1017
00:41:40,690 --> 00:41:43,090
Communication Association President

1018
00:41:43,170 --> 00:41:45,190
of Instant Success Folk Culture?

1019
00:41:46,360 --> 00:41:48,280
General Agent for the China Region

1020
00:41:48,280 --> 00:41:49,670
of Kaidila Co., Ltd.?

1021
00:41:50,980 --> 00:41:53,380
Kaidila China...

1022
00:41:54,280 --> 00:41:55,940
Mr. Qu's agent.
[T/N: pun on "Mr. Qu" and "Region & General"]

1023
00:41:55,940 --> 00:41:57,400
He was Mr. Qu's chauffeur.

1024
00:41:57,920 --> 00:41:59,150
I just figured it out.

1025
00:41:59,150 --> 00:42:00,460
You changed jobs again.

1026
00:42:00,460 --> 00:42:01,730
Let me see what this job is.

1027
00:42:01,730 --> 00:42:02,710
The capable are kept busy.

1028
00:42:02,710 --> 00:42:04,530
General Manager of

1029
00:42:04,550 --> 00:42:05,820
Destined to Meet Co., Ltd.,

1030
00:42:05,820 --> 00:42:06,730
Lucky Ma.

1031
00:42:06,800 --> 00:42:07,650
Aren't you Ma Xiaojun?

1032
00:42:07,650 --> 00:42:08,750
Why'd you change your name?

1033
00:42:08,750 --> 00:42:09,650
I had a fortune teller pick it.

1034
00:42:09,650 --> 00:42:10,450
For good luck.

1035
00:42:10,480 --> 00:42:11,980
May good luck always come my way.

1036
00:42:11,980 --> 00:42:13,860
Then what's with the symbols down here?

1037
00:42:13,140 --> 00:42:14,150
[Destined to Meet Co., Ltd.,]

1038
00:42:13,980 --> 00:42:14,670
You don't understand, right?

1039
00:42:14,180 --> 00:42:15,090
[General Manager: Lucky Ma]

1040
00:42:15,280 --> 00:42:16,940
Uneducated. This is Russian.

1041
00:42:17,340 --> 00:42:19,000
So it's international trade.

1042
00:42:19,230 --> 00:42:19,840
Exactly.

1043
00:42:21,030 --> 00:42:21,570
Jun.

1044
00:42:22,920 --> 00:42:24,030
Tell me the truth.

1045
00:42:24,710 --> 00:42:25,280
Are you

1046
00:42:25,280 --> 00:42:26,610
in some kind of trouble?

1047
00:42:26,760 --> 00:42:27,900
If you need money,

1048
00:42:28,500 --> 00:42:29,900
even though I don't have any,

1049
00:42:29,900 --> 00:42:30,880
you know my mom, right?

1050
00:42:30,880 --> 00:42:32,480
I can ask her to lend you some.

1051
00:42:32,880 --> 00:42:33,740
You can scam me,

1052
00:42:34,230 --> 00:42:35,690
but don't scam my friends.

1053
00:42:36,510 --> 00:42:36,940
Hey.

1054
00:42:37,010 --> 00:42:37,840
Even if I scammed you,

1055
00:42:37,840 --> 00:42:39,070
I wouldn't scam

1056
00:42:39,070 --> 00:42:40,470
these newly met friends.

1057
00:42:40,760 --> 00:42:41,780
Besides, Liangliang,

1058
00:42:41,780 --> 00:42:42,660
let's swear

1059
00:42:42,730 --> 00:42:43,790
by the light.

1060
00:42:44,300 --> 00:42:44,900
Be honest.

1061
00:42:45,400 --> 00:42:46,660
Have I ever scammed you

1062
00:42:47,210 --> 00:42:48,470
throughout the years?

1063
00:42:48,570 --> 00:42:49,070
No.

1064
00:42:49,920 --> 00:42:51,440
Have I ever scammed

1065
00:42:51,440 --> 00:42:52,670
any of your friends?

1066
00:42:52,760 --> 00:42:53,980
No to that either.

1067
00:42:54,090 --> 00:42:55,720
I'm reliable!
